title: Riverheads overcomes Luray in four sets
text:
Riverheads overcomes Luray in four sets Staff Report 9:13 p.m. EDT October 8, 2015 File CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
LURAY â€” Riverheads improved to 12-1 Thursday with a four-set victory over Luray. 
The Gladiators started off slowly, dropping the first set 13-25, before running over the Bulldogs in the next three 25-22, 25-19 and 25-18. 
Emma Casto led the team with 15 kills and 16 digs. Cassidey Chrisman added a strong effort with 10 kills and 16 digs. Kelly Coffey had three aces, five kills, and a team-high 25 assists. Blake Bartley added six kills and 26 digs. Madison Cash had a team-high 28 digs, and McKenze Taylor had five kills. 
In the JV game Luray came out on top in straight sets 25-14 and 25-17. 
Riverheads will be back in action Monday, hosting Stonewall Jackson. Read or Share this story: http://www.newsleader.com/story/sports/high-school/2015/10/08/riverheads-overcomes-luray-four-sets/73622544/ TOP VIDEOS
